.\" Manpage for podmgr.
.TH PODMGR 1 "2026-07-11" "podmgr 1.0.5" "Rootless Podman system user manager"
.SH NAME
podmgr \- create and manage least-privileged host users for rootless Podman workloads
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B podmgr
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.RB [ \-\-
.IR cmd ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B podmgr
provisions and operates dedicated, least-privileged system users, each running
its own rootless Podman instance. Every managed user receives an isolated home,
a subordinate UID/GID range (allocated and committed via
.BR fsubid (1)),
.B systemd
user-session linger, and a workload unit generated from a
.B podman compose
template or, when available, from Podman Quadlet sources.
.PP
The intent is per-workload isolation: a separate host user per trust boundary so
that a container escape is contained to a single unprivileged account rather
than the operator's primary user.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS User lifecycle
.TP
.B setup
Create the system user and configure rootless Podman. Fails if the user already
exists; use
.B reinstall
to reconfigure. Requires root.
.TP
.B cleanup
Stop the workload, remove the user, and delete all associated state. Operates
only on users carrying podmgr's marker file. Requires root.
.TP
.B reinstall
Run
.B cleanup
followed by
.BR setup .
Requires root.
.TP
.B list
List containers across all managed users. With
.B \-\-all
include stopped containers.
.TP
.B info
Show one user's provisioning state: UID/GID, subuid/subgid range, linger,
compose directory, marker, and container count.
.TP
.B status
Report whether the user's workload service and Podman socket are active.
.SS Podman engine
.TP
.B up
Start the workload
.RB ( "podman compose up -d" ).
.RS
Before execution,
.B podmgr
validates that the compose directory exists, is owned by the target user, and
that
.I COMPOSE_FILE
exists and is readable by that user. When
.I COMPOSE_FILE
is set to
.I compose.yaml
or
.I compose.yml
, podmgr also accepts the other extension as a fallback.
.RE
.TP
.B down
Stop the workload
.RB ( "podman compose down" ).
.RS
Uses the same compose preflight checks as
.BR up .
.RE
.TP
.B restart
Stop then start the workload.
.TP
.B ps
Show running containers.
.TP
.B stats
Show a one-shot resource table per container. With
.B \-\-df
also report disk usage.
.TP
.B prune
Reclaim space by removing unused containers, images, and networks. With
.B \-\-all
also remove unused images; with
.B \-\-volumes
also remove unused volumes.
.SS User session
.TP
.B shell
Open an interactive shell in the managed host user's session.
.RS
Commands that run with a compose working directory (for example
.BR shell ", " run ", " exec ", and " run-in )
validate compose directory ownership and accessibility first.
.RE
.TP
.B run \-\- \fIcmd\fR ...
Run an arbitrary command in the managed host user's session.
.TP
.B start \fR/\fB stop \fR/\fB kill
Start or stop the user's workload service.
.B kill
is an alias of
.BR stop .
.TP
.B journal
Follow the user's journal. Requires root or membership in the
.B systemd-journal
group.
.SS Container access
.TP
.B exec
Open an interactive shell inside a running container, selecting
.B bash
or
.B sh
automatically. If no container is named, the first running one is used.
.TP
.B run\-in \-n \fIc\fB \-\- \fIcmd\fR ...
Run a non-interactive command inside container
.IR c .
.TP
.B clogs \-n \fIc
Follow a container's logs.
.TP
.B cp \-\- \fIsrc dst
Copy files to or from a container
.RB ( "podman cp" ).
.TP
.B top \-n \fIc
Show the process table inside a container.
.SS Compose file management
.TP
.B adopt \-f \fIpath
Copy a local file or directory into the user's compose directory and set
ownership to the target user.
.SS Subordinate IDs
.TP
.B subid
Show the user's committed subuid/subgid allocation, as reported by
.BR fsubid (1).
.TP
.B subid\-check
Audit subordinate ID files for gaps and overlaps (delegated to
.BR fsubid (1)).
.TP
.B subid\-reclaim
Garbage-collect ranges of deleted users and stale reservations (delegated to
.BR fsubid (1)).
.SS Other
.TP
.B version
Print the podmgr version.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-user " " \fIname\fR
Target system username. Required for all commands except
.BR list ", " subid\-check ", " subid\-reclaim ", and " version .
Must match
.BR [a\-z_][a\-z0\-9_\-]{0,31} .
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-compose\-dir " " \fIpath\fR
Compose directory (default
.IR PODMGR_BASE_DIR /compose/ \fIuser\fR).
Must be absolute and inside
.IR PODMGR_BASE_DIR .
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-container " " \fIname\fR
Target container for
.BR exec ", " run\-in ", " clogs ", and " top .
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
For
.BR list ,
include stopped containers; for
.BR prune ,
also remove unused images.
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-volumes
For
.BR prune ,
also remove unused volumes.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-df
For
.BR stats ,
also show disk usage.
.TP
.BR \-j ", " \-\-json
For
.BR list " and " users ,
emit JSON output.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-file " " \fIpath\fR
Source path for
.B adopt .
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-
Pass all following arguments verbatim to the target command
.RB ( run ", " run\-in ", " cp ).
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B podmgr
reads
.I /etc/podmgr.conf
if present.
.RS
.TP
.B LOG_DEST
.BR file ", " journal ", or " both
(default
.BR file ).
.TP
.B LOG_FILE
Log file path (default
.IR /var/log/podmgr.log ).
.TP
.B PODMGR_BASE_DIR
Base directory under which compose directories must reside (default
.IR /srv/podmgr ).
.TP
.B COMPOSE_FILE
Compose file name (default
.IR compose.yaml ).
.TP
.B USE_QUADLET
Prefer Podman Quadlet for unit generation when available.
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/podmgr.conf
Optional configuration.
.TP
.IR /var/lib/ user
Managed user home and marker file.
.TP
.IR /srv/podmgr
Shared base directory owned by the dedicated
.B podmgr
system user and group; the invoking sudo operator is added to that group when
its identity can be validated from the sudo environment.
.TP
.IR /srv/podmgr/compose/ user
Default per-user compose directory.
.SH TROUBLESHOOTING
.TP
.B compose-dir does not exist
Create the user first with
.BR "podmgr setup -u <user>" ,
or pass an existing path with
.BR --compose-dir .
.TP
.B compose-dir must be owned by '<user>'
Fix ownership of the per-user compose directory.
.TP
.B compose file must be owned by '<user>'
Fix ownership of
.I COMPOSE_FILE
inside the compose directory.
.TP
.B compose-dir is not traversable / compose file is not readable
Restore owner mode bits (directory owner execute bit, file owner read bit).
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success and non-zero on error. Lifecycle commands abort and roll
back partial setup on failure.
.SH SECURITY
.B podmgr
invokes external tools by absolute path with a sanitized environment and never
passes user-controlled strings through a shell. Subordinate ID allocation and
commit are delegated to
.BR fsubid (1),
which is the authoritative owner of
.IR /etc/subuid " and " /etc/subgid .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR fsubid (1),
.BR podman (1),
.BR podman\-compose (1),
.BR loginctl (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Amine Tbaik <tbaik.amine@gmail.com>
